In German language, the English term "feasible" is not just translated as "möglich", but also translated as "machbar" while using it with reference to the feasibility or "Machbarkeit" of a project. Therefore, a correct translation of the word when referring to the feasilility of a project would be "machbar". A "feasibility study" will then be a "Machbarkeits-Studie". The English term "Feasibility study" is widely used as well.
